[thinking] **Considering metadata generation challenges**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m pondering whether harness adds test classes automatically. It seems like many tests serialize the model. Since there's no metadata for jaxb-impl yet, tests are causing that generation. Maybe the user-code-filter should include only certain packages for generated library metadata. It looks like test classes aren't included, but the TCK possibly auto-includes application classes. If the native image sees application code at build time, it may not reflect the metadata needed for deeper access.
[thinking] 
[thinking] **Exploring user-code-filter implications**
[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m figuring out that the user-code-filter excludes all `com.sun` entries to prevent app metadata from entering library metadata. However, test classes in the native image might be unregistered. Perhaps Gradle TCK includes agent output unfiltered during native compilation while storing the filtered results. Alright, I need to ensure tests use the public API without relying on direct reflection or serialization. I also want to avoid deprecated methods, so checking with `javap` might be a good idea.
[thinking] 
[assistant-event] thinking_end
