[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering JAXB configuration**\n\nThe user mentioned updating `build.gradle` only if we need runtime arguments. Am I sure we need them? For JAXB RI on newer Java, it seems like it wants to define optimized accessor classes with dynamic loading, which Native Image doesn’t fully support for generating classes at runtime. I should check if the old metadata is present. It seems like JAXB may use optimized accessors by default, but regular JAXB should work if it's disabled. Should I set the system property in our tests?\n\n**Clarifying JAXB behavior**\n\nAccording to the rules, I need to catch errors during test exercises that require dynamic class loading to verify behavior. However, JAXB's optimized accessor is more of an implementation detail than a core library function, which raises the question: can we bypass this with a documented property? I wonder if `ClassTailor.noOptimize` is public or not. I should check how to handle this optimized behavior in my testing.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_045b521fb3dcf2f9016a26c946b55c8193af5cf6db73c9d876\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqJslgIKD4dNUEcPU_1jAeBXX75uigb0K-BE3fKwhk_wvxuWwut6V5WKg3QJfxNTyfYO-m1VViUMZe9n118BU8wFYAxjn4Jkax8z5DgkQ5XQzHa6siIrHsHFLTQ1CcabwOXKuwPWgRpWc-vJVjUzLYQft0cuYA7D0p2SpojMIL58-p12sN7IGDNbcwIvNOtKk8kSaw3K3u4s1ud1JwIguCU3sWSkf1Ts1srxuurJpBpL_v58fTXnj4JOSXxI9-lzWyZYA8ELjqkAoWmS2Z53mXfjBYJGpbN4Yc5FStZn0eRoIP1WjV3ke7ajqFsqqkdnI_vtR3NJSPOiSZ7yhfr1bo_A4zulYDvL8F1BlNgNIxjVGaBq5VIDlgf_h0E3KnZJHjjf7Q8XAyX_B291aW-JPWbo85_g5Y2IZv4tb7H8aASkFWIGyI9wlVN4u2Vd7qwGV9DtrPCWx92xtAPIktjz_mTErkKpHVBfcasZAzq5P7btUO1l1WsyT5wWxZxZAd05-NvrLLR8Q-mI1hl15SqsJqf0qes4vqzcwP9K9pMpP2UVw04DYIeUkJRFU6XhiThIEEZWcC9sMlr2eTvFsmZkUz1W-IWldm47BR29LkKiD5HcQ3msFBE6SVhQnLT0-LX8ee_v1S0kHunJM7-hbc143g0fw27TMDQ3U3lwSzrWdHEnZiPkArAMJ86lyIy79y1kfCgcDg1ue4T-IUTi0HQSWzjqAyqY_afBNGviiZsWe1nGMKyz9